    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nLSP floating hover window, whose purpose is to display read-only documentation, has `concealcursor` set to `''` which causes concealed characters/lines to be shown while reading documentation.\nOther non-editable UI windows in Neovim, such as `gO` outlines, set `concealcursor='nc'` to avoid showing concealed text when the user browses the table of content. because the intended behavior matches that. \n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2246e3c3-6471-4044-942b-6f0194ab5e67\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBy default, LSP hover windows (and other relevant windows) should set `concealcursor = 'nc'` (or `'n'` ?)",
